does anyone know how to make basmati rice any help would be greatly appreciated thanks again basmati rice seasoned with garam masala cups basmati rice tablespoons butter medium size onions chopped clove garlic minced teaspoon garam masala salt freshly ground black pepper to taste cups vegetable broth in a medium stove to oven pot melt butter over medium heat add chopped onions garlic and garam masala and cook to minutes stirring until onions are softened add rice and stir until well coated add vegetable stock salt and pepper to taste bring to a boil cover and bake in the oven until the rice is tender and the stock is absorbed about to minutes let stand covered for minutes before serving enjoy Risotto Chili con carne Curry Haggis Gumbo Cantonese cuisine Jewish cuisine Chicken soup Tea Barbecue French fries Rice pudding Cajun cuisine Bengali cuisine Halva Rice Ramen Dumpling Cuisine of Brazil Korean cuisine Russian cuisine Bread German cuisine Pizza Hamburger Soul food Soup Hot dog Peruvian cuisine Kebab Coffee Mayonnaise Cuisine of the Philippines Roast beef Dosa Nabemono Cincinnati chili Turkish coffee Hot pot In-N-Out Burger Punjabi cuisine Cuisine of India D__ner kebab Cuisine of Malaysia Stir frying Kelantan Cookware and bakeware Cuisine of Greece Satay Garlic French cuisine Kraft Dinner Bacon Peanut butter Chocolate Cuisine of Laos Bagel Ice cream Pasta Chowder Paella MRE Cuisine of the Southern United States Baking Vinegar Tortilla Onion Tamale Ketchup Beef noodle soup Stock (food) B__chamel sauce Flour Cuisine of Africa Breakfast Common bean Vegetarian cuisine Rice congee Cuisine of Ethiopia Roman eating and drinking Bearnaise sauce Cuisine of Turkey Miso Pickling Mashed potato Potato Yoghurt 